{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s50_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Age-Related Macular Degeneration"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"121b4c",
"children":[
"Age-Related Macular Degeneration"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a7efb2",
"children":[
"Dry ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"age-related macular degeneration",
"children":[
"AMD"
]
},
" involves the deposition of extracellular material (drusen) in the macular region of one or both eyes and may cause diminished visual acuity. Smoking cessation is imperative. Progression of advanced dry AMD may be slowed with the use of zinc or antioxidant supplements."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"49e657",
"children":[
"A small percentage of patients with dry AMD will progress to develop new vessel growth under the retina (wet AMD). Bleeding and exudation results in sudden (or rapid onset over weeks), painless blurring or warping of central vision. Laser photocoagulation and intraocular injection of ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"vascular endothelial growth factor",
"children":[
"VEGF"
]
},
" inhibitors are recommended for wet AMD."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s50_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Retinal Detachment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"cd29bb",
"children":[
"Retinal Detachment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b14a5b",
"children":[
"Retinal detachment occurs mainly in myopic patients. Symptoms are floaters, flashes of light (photopsias), and squiggly lines, followed by a sudden, peripheral visual field defect that resembles a black curtain and progresses across the entire visual field. Emergent ophthalmology referral is crucial, as prognosis depends on the time to surgical treatment."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s50_5",
"title":{
"__html":"Primary Open-Angle Glaucoma"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b693a6",
"children":[
"Primary Open-Angle Glaucoma"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a2a99a",
"children":[
"Primary open-angle glaucoma is characterized by decreased aqueous flow with a normal iridocorneal angle. Peripheral visual field loss is the earliest symptom, but it frequently goes unreported, and progression to central vision loss occurs in untreated patients. Treatment focuses on decreasing intraocular pressure with surgery or medications."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s50_6",
"title":{
"__html":"Cataracts"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"6bdaea",
"children":[
"Cataracts"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"83f4d2",
"children":[
"Cataracts frequently cause glare sensitivity and vision impairment, particularly at night. Examination reveals lens opacification along with diminished or absent red reflex. Treatment for vision-impairing cataracts includes phacoemulsification with intraoperative lens replacement."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s50_7",
"title":{
"__html":"Dry Eye"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"50de9c",
"children":[
"Dry Eye"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"8fe5ee",
"children":[
"Dry eye (keratoconjunctivitis sicca) results from abnormal eye lubrication. Symptoms are usually bilateral and include ocular pain, foreign-body sensation, light sensitivity, tearing, and irritation/redness. Treatment includes artificial tears and, occasionally, punctal occlusion/plugs. Consider Sjögren syndrome."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gm_s50_8",
"title":{
"__html":"Corneal Abrasions"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"00d08a",
"children":[
"Corneal Abrasions"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"bfb783",
"children":[
"Corneal abrasions are superficial epithelial defects that result from mechanical trauma, foreign bodies, and contact lens use. Symptoms include severe eye pain, foreign-body sensation, light sensitivity, and tearing. Fluorescein should be performed in all patients along with visual acuity assessment; provide immediate ophthalmology referral for vision loss. In contact lens wearers, topical antibiotics should be given. Eye patches are generally avoided."
]
}
]
}
]
},
